00:00:02:060000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:00:02:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:02:060000.Dialogue: Why do I always have to carry the heavy stuff?

00:00:04:220000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:00:04:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:04:220000.Dialogue: Well, it's very simple. In our ragtag band of scientists with nothing to lose, I'm the smart one, Wolowitz is the funny one, and Koothrappali is the lovable foreigner who struggles to understand our ways and fails.

00:00:18:120000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:00:18:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:18:120000.Dialogue: That leaves you, by default, as the muscle.

00:00:20:220000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:00:20:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:20:220000.Dialogue: Oh. One more floor, and I'd be the pulled muscle.

00:00:26:070000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:00:26:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:26:070000.Dialogue: Oh, it's about time. I'm starving.

00:00:28:220000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:00:28:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:28:220000.Dialogue: Um, well, we didn't actually get Chinese food.

00:00:31:120000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:00:31:120000.Speaker: Leonard

00:00:34:030000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:00:34:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:34:030000.Dialogue: Oh, no. You didn't trade the food for magic beans, did you?

00:00:37:150000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:00:37:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:37:150000.Dialogue: Of course not. And technically, magic beans would be food. Although eating them would be quite a waste, since you could plant them, and overnight, have a giant beanstalk, which would provide enough roughage for a small city.

00:00:50:030000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:00:50:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:50:030000.Dialogue: Yeah, sometimes I don't listen. Sometimes I just watch your jaw go up and down.

00:00:56:060000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:00:56:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:56:060000.Dialogue: We were on our way to the Chinese restaurant when we thought we saw Adam West, so we followed him.

00:01:00:130000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:00:130000.Speaker: Penny

00:01:01:160000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:01:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:01:160000.Dialogue: Who's Adam West?! Leonard, what do the two of you talk about after the coitus?

00:01:08:140000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:08:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:08:140000.Dialogue: My guess is, "Hey, four minutes! New record!"

00:01:13:140000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:13:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:13:140000.Dialogue: That's why I'm the funny one.

00:01:17:130000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:17:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:17:130000.Dialogue: Anyway, we followed the guy to this garage sale, and they had the coolest stuff.

00:01:21:140000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:21:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:21:140000.Dialogue: They were closing up. We got this whole box for 60 bucks.

00:01:24:130000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:24:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:24:130000.Dialogue: We didn't even get to go through it all. There could be anything in here.

00:01:27:060000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:27:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:27:060000.Dialogue: There a new girlfriend in there? 'Cause you might need one.

00:01:29:230000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:29:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:29:230000.Dialogue: No. But there is an original final draft Ghostbusters script with actual slime stains! Oh, you're right. It's Ghostbusters 2. Never mind.

00:01:41:230000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:41:230000.Speaker: Howard

00:01:47:230000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:47:230000.Speaker: Howard

00:01:51:090000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:01:51:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:51:090000.Dialogue: When I was 11, my mother got me one to help me sleep after my dad left. I used to pretend that my dad had moved to the planet Melmac, and Alf was going to bring him back to me. But he never did. Where's my daddy, puppet?

00:02:13:190000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:02:13:190000.Speaker: Howard

00:02:16:200000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:02:16:200000.Speaker: Penny

00:02:18:200000.Scene: The stairwell. Leonard is carrying a large box.
00:02:18:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:18:200000.Dialogue: No, what's sad is that you don't know Adam West was TV's Batman.

00:02:51:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:51:130000.Dialogue: Here's Spock's head with no body.

00:02:56:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:56:010000.Dialogue: Here's Mr. T's body with no head.

00:03:00:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:00:190000.Dialogue: Oh, yeah, here's Spock's body with Mr. T's head.

00:03:06:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:06:070000.Dialogue: I pity the fool who's illogical.

00:03:11:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:03:11:100000.Dialogue: Okay, I'm just gonna go home and make a grilled cheese and window-shop on eHarmony.

00:03:22:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:22:210000.Dialogue: Ooh, look, an Indiana Jones connect-the-dots.

00:03:28:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:28:110000.Dialogue: Looks like someone drew a penis on him.

00:03:41:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:41:190000.Dialogue: You see what you're doing? Stop that.

00:03:49:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:49:060000.Dialogue: It appears to be a Lord of the Rings ring.

00:03:51:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:51:160000.Dialogue: It's even got the Elvish engraving on it.

00:03:54:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:54:180000.Dialogue: It's not Elvish. It's the language of Mordor written in Elvish script.

00:04:18:080000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:18:080000.Dialogue: So, I was doing some checking on the ring.

00:04:20:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:04:20:120000.Dialogue: Hold on. Sheldon, is there ketchup on that table?

00:04:22:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:22:180000.Dialogue: Yes, there is. Oh, here's a fun fact. Ketchup started out as a general term for sauce, typically made of mushrooms or fish brine with herbs and spices. Some popular early main ingredients included blueberry, anchovy, oyster, kidney bean and grape.

00:04:40:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:04:40:100000.Dialogue: No, that's okay. I'll get it.

00:04:43:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:43:030000.Dialogue: Listen, I was looking at the ring, and it seemed a little weird. No copyright notice on it. So, I took it down to this buddy of mine who deals with-- shall we say-- the seedy underbelly of the collectibles world.

00:04:57:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:57:210000.Dialogue: You know, your black market phasers, your screen-worn Lieutenant Uhura panties, that kind of stuff.

00:05:05:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:05:05:230000.Dialogue: Who's this mysterious buddy you suddenly have?

00:05:07:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:07:230000.Dialogue: Just a guy. I know a guy.

00:05:12:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:05:12:180000.Dialogue: Who else could it be? It has to be Eddie Crispo.

00:05:14:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:14:090000.Dialogue: I know lots of dangerous people, okay?

00:05:19:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:19:130000.Dialogue: Anyway, he said this isn't a replica. It's the real deal.

00:05:25:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:25:160000.Dialogue: If you're suggesting that that is the actual ring of power forged by Sauron in Mount Doom, I look at you with an expression of exhaustion and ever so slight amusement.

00:05:38:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:38:100000.Dialogue: He's not saying it's a magic ring. You're not, are you?

00:05:43:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:43:060000.Dialogue: No, but it's close. Look at the markings inside. Those are production markings. Nine rings were made for use in the Lord of the Rings movies. Three were given to members of the cast. The rest were destroyed. Except one. One was stolen. Gentlemen... this is the one ring.

00:06:11:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:11:160000.Dialogue: No, it is not yours. We all went in on the box together.

00:06:14:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:14:140000.Dialogue: Well, yes, but I found it in the box, and the laws of maritime salvage clearly state that the finder of a sunken treasure is the owner of the treasure.

00:06:24:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:24:100000.Dialogue: Other than the lack of water, how is it not?

00:06:26:200000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:26:200000.Dialogue: Wait, wait. Sheldon, stop being crazy for a second. How much is something like this worth?

00:06:31:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:31:130000.Dialogue: Well, it's tough to say since it's hot, but on the underground market, my guy figures...

00:06:45:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:45:090000.Dialogue: Okay, that's a lot of money. The wise thing to do is invest it in something practical. Like a jet ski.

00:06:51:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:51:180000.Dialogue: Why do you want a jet ski?

00:06:54:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:54:180000.Dialogue: All the wealthy and beautiful people in movies ride Jet Skis. That can't just be a coincidence.

00:07:00:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:00:190000.Dialogue: We can't sell it. We have to keep it and love it and polish it, and only take it out occasionally when we go to the park and reenact our favorite scenes from the movies.

00:07:10:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:10:160000.Dialogue: It's sad how great that sounds.

00:07:14:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:14:180000.Dialogue: Guys, it's stolen. It should go back to Peter Jackson. He made the movies; it belongs to him.

00:07:19:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:19:090000.Dialogue: WOLOWITZ: Fine. He can have it back as long as he promises to make me a hobbit in his next movie.

00:07:27:080000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:27:080000.Dialogue: Clearly, you've never been to my house for dinner on Rosh Hashanah.

00:07:31:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:31:110000.Dialogue: We are not blackmailing Peter J... All right, where's the ring?

00:07:38:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:38:180000.Dialogue: The ring was unguarded. It was just sitting on the table. Anyone could have taken it. Proof? I did.

00:07:52:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:52:230000.Dialogue: I found it. The ring is mine. I don't understand why in this group I never get my way.

00:08:04:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:04:150000.Dialogue: I'll stipulate to that if you give me the ring.

00:08:08:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:08:220000.Dialogue: Hey, guys. Enjoying your food that I actually brought you instead of promising food, but bringing you a box of random crap?

00:08:16:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:16:050000.Dialogue: Yeah, it's delicious. The sarcasm's a little stale, though.

00:08:20:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:20:080000.Dialogue: Hey, how about this? Until we figure out what to do with the ring, Penny holds on to it.

00:08:31:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:31:230000.Dialogue: Will you hold on to this for a couple of days?

00:08:34:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:34:070000.Dialogue: It's a prop from a movie, and we're kind of fighting over it.

00:08:37:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:37:220000.Dialogue: Okay, just to be clear, the first piece of jewelry my boyfriend gives me is a prop from a movie, and I don't even get to keep it?

00:08:43:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:43:190000.Dialogue: If you had gone out with me three years ago, by now, you'd have my great Aunt Ida's brooch that she smuggled out of occupied Belgium in a cat.

00:10:06:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:06:170000.Dialogue: Sheldon tried to take the ring and I punched him.

As he tries to remove it, she wakes up, screams, and punches him in the face.
00:10:09:160000.Speaker: Leonard

00:10:18:080000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:18:080000.Dialogue: So, Sheldon, how's it feel to get beaten up by a girl?

00:10:26:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:26:090000.Dialogue: It's not the first time. I have a twin sister whose assaults began in utero.

00:10:32:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:32:210000.Dialogue: If only I'd had the presence of mind to reabsorb her, then I'd have a mole with hair in it instead of a tedious yearly Christmas letter.

00:10:41:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:41:080000.Dialogue: Gentlemen, have you come to the realization that the only reasonable course of action is to sell the ring and divide the money?

00:10:48:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:48:120000.Dialogue: I was afraid of that. Go ahead.

00:10:53:130000.Speaker: Man on Screen
00:10:53:130000.Dialogue: Greetings from Mumbai. I am Raj's attorney, Venkatesh Koothrappali.

00:11:01:050000.Speaker: Venkatesh
00:11:01:050000.Dialogue: Don't answer that. I'll get straight to the point. My client's prepared to surrender any interest he has in the ring in exchange for two Kawasaki Jet Skis.

00:11:10:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:10:150000.Dialogue: We're not giving him two Jet Skis.

00:11:13:160000.Speaker: Venkatesh
00:11:13:160000.Dialogue: Look, we're big boys, why don't we just cut to the chase and meet in the middle? One Kawasaki Jet Ski. Done and done.

00:11:24:230000.Speaker: Venkatesh
00:11:24:230000.Dialogue: All right, forget the Jet Skis.

00:11:27:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:27:020000.Dialogue: Forget the Jet Skis? That was our line in the sand! What happened to "tear them a new one?"

00:11:31:180000.Speaker: Venkatesh
00:11:31:180000.Dialogue: What can I say? They played hardball. We lost.

00:11:36:220000.Speaker: Venkatesh
00:11:36:220000.Dialogue: I told you that when you hired me.

00:11:44:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:44:110000.Dialogue: Okay, just so you know, if we're bringing in cousins who are lawyers, prepare for shock and awe.

00:11:51:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:51:030000.Dialogue: You know what? I am ending this. Penny didn't want to hold the ring anymore. She gave it to me. I have it. I'm sending it back. Where's the ring?

00:12:02:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:02:130000.Dialogue: Next time be aware of your surroundings while urinating in a public men's room.

00:12:11:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:11:200000.Dialogue: Okay, now, this is ridiculous! Then let go! I'm not letting go. You let go.

00:12:15:010000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:15:010000.Dialogue: I say this ring belongs to the last person who can hold on.

00:12:18:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:18:140000.Dialogue: Fine. But can't we go home and start this?

00:12:20:190000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:20:190000.Dialogue: Sure. Let go of the ring.

00:12:29:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:29:200000.Dialogue: You do realize there's a giant bug movie marathon tonight on the Syfy Channel.

00:13:02:110000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:13:02:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:02:110000.Dialogue: You know, there's a point when this becomes idiotic.

00:13:05:090000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:13:05:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:05:090000.Dialogue: And it wasn't when we were driving like this?

00:13:09:210000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:13:09:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:09:210000.Dialogue: I would advise the three of you that resistance is futile. I have endless patience. I once spent two-and-a-half hours on hold with Hewlett-Packard customer service just to complain about their customer service.

00:13:24:020000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:13:24:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:24:020000.Dialogue: You want to talk about endless patience? Penny made me watch all five seasons of Sex and the City.

00:13:32:100000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:13:32:100000.Speaker: Raj

00:13:34:100000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:13:34:100000.Speaker: Leonard

00:13:38:010000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:13:38:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:13:38:010000.Dialogue: No, no, no, the sixth season is great. We go to Paris with Carrie and get our heart broken, and then Mr. Big shows up, we don't know if we can trust him again. It's a wild ride.

00:13:52:100000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:13:52:100000.Speaker: Leonard

00:14:00:110000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:14:00:110000.Speaker: Raj

00:14:10:200000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:14:10:200000.Speaker: Raj

00:14:15:210000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:14:15:210000.Speaker: Penny

00:14:18:230000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:14:18:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:18:230000.Dialogue: Last one holding the ring decides its fate. I know, it sounds silly.

00:14:23:000000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:14:23:000000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:23:000000.Dialogue: No, no, no, no, no, you are my boyfriend. Nothing you do is silly to me.

00:14:26:230000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:14:26:230000.Speaker: Leonard

00:14:28:220000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:14:28:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:28:220000.Dialogue: FYI-- this is a bag from Victoria's Secret.

00:14:39:200000.Scene: The stairwell. The guys are coming up the stairs, all still holding the ring.
00:14:39:200000.Speaker: Leonard

00:14:52:090000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:14:52:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:52:090000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, Ma, I have to stay late at the office.

00:14:56:090000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:14:56:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:56:090000.Dialogue: No, he's doesn't! He's lying to you!

00:14:59:200000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:14:59:200000.Speaker: Howard

00:15:01:120000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:15:01:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:01:120000.Dialogue: Well, if you want privacy let go of the ring. I'm so glad we came to this gentile strip club!

00:15:08:010000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:15:08:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:08:010000.Dialogue: Howard, here's more bacon to tuck into the shiksa's G-string!

00:15:14:140000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:15:14:140000.Speaker: Howard

00:15:16:120000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:15:16:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:16:120000.Dialogue: I think it's lovely you call your mommy and let her know you're going to be late for dinner. From what I know about these things, if a woman doesn't breast-feed on time, it's very uncomfortable for her boobies.

00:15:26:090000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:15:26:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:26:090000.Dialogue: Don't you talk about my mother's boobies!

00:15:29:100000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:15:29:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:29:100000.Dialogue: If you're offended, let go of the ring and go on home to your mother's boobies.

00:15:33:140000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:15:33:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:33:140000.Dialogue: Excellent, excellent. Tire each other out, the ring will be mine. Howard, why don't you go after Raj's mother?

00:15:39:180000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:15:39:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:39:180000.Dialogue: Why don't we go after your mother?

00:15:43:060000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:15:43:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:43:060000.Dialogue: Go ahead. I have no illusions about my mother. She is a kind, loving, religiously fanatical right-wing Texan with a slightly out-of-scale head and a mild Dr. Pepper addiction.

00:15:56:160000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:15:56:160000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:15:59:040000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:15:59:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:59:040000.Dialogue: That's not gonna get you anywhere. Better pull out the big gun.

00:16:02:170000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
00:16:02:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:02:170000.Dialogue: You're right. Let's talk about your grandmother.

00:16:05:220000.Scene: The apartment. The three guys are still holding the ring. Howard is on the phone.
